# Optional: full origin of the Harvested API (no trailing slash).
# Leave unset during local dev to use Vite’s proxy → http://127.0.0.1:3001
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.example.com

# Local backend (see package.json):
#   npm run api          → waitlist API only on :3001
#   npm run dev          → Vite only (proxy /api → :3001 if API is running)
#   npm run dev:all      → API + Vite together

# --- Production on Vercel (pick one storage path)
#
# A) Upstash Redis (simplest for Vercel — no SQL)
#    1) https://console.upstash.com → Redis → create database → copy REST URL + token
#    2) In Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables, add:
#         UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL
#         UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
#         WAITLIST_ADMIN_SECRET  (long random string; required for GET export below)
#    The /api/waitlist and /api/waitlist-signups serverless routes use these automatically.
#
# B) Local dev: run `npm run api` (no Upstash needed). Data file: server/data/waitlist.json
#
# C) Optional: same Node API with Supabase instead of the JSON file (omit Upstash on Vercel if you use this on a host that runs Node)
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...   # server only, never in Vite
#
# List signups:
#   • Browser table: open /waitlist-admin.html on your site → paste WAITLIST_ADMIN_SECRET → “Show table”
#   • JSON: GET .../api/waitlist-signups  Header: X-Admin-Secret: <WAITLIST_ADMIN_SECRET>
# WAITLIST_ADMIN_SECRET=use-a-long-random-string
#
# Pilot progress bar: optional override (0–100). If unset, uses PILOT_SLOTS_CLAIMED in api/waitlist-pilot-capacity.mjs + server/waitlist-api.mjs
# PILOT_CLAIMED_MANUAL=41
#
# Supabase SQL (only if using C): waitlist-signups-supabase.sql (+ waitlist-signups-add-name-column.sql if needed)
